	<videoContent >
			 <videos path="content/eng/video/Social_Media.mp4" poster="content/eng/video/Social_Media.jpg" width="640" height="360" >
				<cc time="0" ><![CDATA[]]></cc>
				<cc time="0" ><![CDATA[Would you tell a stranger on the street your name?]]></cc>
				<cc time="4" ><![CDATA[Your date of birth?]]></cc>
				<cc time="5" ><![CDATA[Where you live?]]></cc> 
				<cc time="7" ><![CDATA[Where you work?]]></cc> 
				<cc time="9" ><![CDATA[The routes you take?]]></cc> 
				<cc time="11" ><![CDATA[Who your friends are?]]></cc> 
				<cc time="12" ><![CDATA[Your relationship status?]]></cc> 
				<cc time="15" ><![CDATA[Your emotional state? ]]></cc> 
				<cc time="16" ><![CDATA[Probably not. ]]></cc> 
				<cc time="17" ><![CDATA[But if you are a social media user, you have probably made some or all of this information available to potentially thousands of strangers online.]]></cc> 
				<cc time="27" ><![CDATA[Any one of these strangers is potentially a criminal.]]></cc> 
				<cc time="30" ><![CDATA[They can use this information to commit a range of crimes, from identity theft to burglaries and assaults.]]></cc> 
				<cc time="37" ><![CDATA[When you rearrange the word POST, you get STOP.]]></cc> 
				<cc time="40" ><![CDATA[Before you POST anything on a social media site, STOP and think for a minute. ]]></cc> 
				<cc time="46" ><![CDATA[Ask yourself:]]></cc> 
				<cc time="47" ><![CDATA[What does this information reveal about me, the people I know and my employer?]]></cc> 
				<cc time="54" ><![CDATA[Do I really need to share this information publicly?]]></cc> 
				<cc time="57" ><![CDATA[Would I tell a stranger on the street this information?]]></cc> 
				<cc time="60" ><![CDATA[Learn about the privacy settings of your social media accounts. ]]></cc> 
				<cc time="64" ><![CDATA[Only share with trusted connections, and keep a track of what others post about you on their profiles.]]></cc> 
				<cc time="70" ><![CDATA[If you think a friend has posted information about you that you’d rather not have online, ask them to take it down.]]></cc> 
				<cc time="77" ><![CDATA[Examine the contracts you enter into with social media service providers by reading the terms of use.]]></cc> 
				<cc time="83" ><![CDATA[Often the material you upload becomes the property of the service provider.]]></cc> 
				<cc time="87" ><![CDATA[They can hold on to this information indefinitely and use it how they wish.]]></cc> 
				<cc time="93" ><![CDATA[They cannot guarantee that data they hold about you will not be hacked by cybercriminals in the future.]]></cc> 
				<cc time="99" ><![CDATA[Remember, once you post information to a social networking site, it is no longer your private information.]]></cc> 
				<cc time="106" ><![CDATA[The more information you post, the more vulnerable you may become.  ]]></cc> 
				<cc time="111" ><![CDATA[Before you POST,]]></cc> 
				<cc time="112" ><![CDATA[STOP and think.]]></cc> 
